## Ways to Gift Bitcoin (Under $25)

Now they understand Bitcoin conceptually. Time to give them some:

### **SATSCARD by Coinkite** ($20)
<%= cdn_image_tag("blog/bitcoin-gift-christmas-2025-under-25-usd/satscard.jpg", alt: "SATSCARD", class: "w-full max-w-lg mx-auto rounded-lg shadow-lg mb-4") %>

**What it is:** Credit card-sized NFC Bitcoin wallet

**How it works:** Tap phone to card, Bitcoin appears

**The good:** Professional, reusable (up to 10 times), fits in wallet

**The bad:** Needs NFC phone, no instructions included

**Best for:** Tech-comfortable recipients who already understand Bitcoin basics

**‚Üí** [Get it at Coinkite Store](https://store.coinkite.com/store/category/satscard)

---

### **DIY Paper Wallets** (Free-$5)

**What you need:**
* BitAddress.org (download offline)
* Printer (not networked)
* Nice paper ($5)
* Security envelope ($1)

**Process:**
1. Generate offline for security
2. Print private/public keys
3. Fund with $10-20 Bitcoin
4. Seal in tamper-evident envelope

**Warning:** Easy to mess up security. No built-in help for recipients
**‚Üí** [Read my paper wallet printer guide](https://hongbaob.tc/blog/best-inkjet-laser-printer-paper-wallet)

---

### **Physical Bitcoin Coins** ($25)

**Brands:** Denarium, Cryptmint
**Reality:** One-time use novelty items
**How they work:** Peel hologram, reveal private key
**Problem:** Confusing redemption process

Look cool, work poorly. Better as conversation pieces.
**‚Üí** [Check Denarium](https://denarium.com)

---

### **OpenDime USB Sticks** ($15)
<%= cdn_image_tag("blog/bitcoin-gift-christmas-2025-under-25-usd/opendime.jpg", alt: "OpenDime", class: "w-full max-w-lg mx-auto rounded-lg shadow-lg mb-4") %>

**Unique feature:** Bearer instrument like cash
**How it works:** Plug in, generates wallet, break to reveal key
**Downside:** Requires computer, intimidating for newcomers
**‚Üí** [Get OpenDime](https://opendime.com)

---

### **Bitcoin Gift Cards** ($10-25)

**Where:** Coinbase, Bitrefill, CoinCards
**The catch:** Not real Bitcoin until redeemed
**Issues:** KYC requirements, expiration dates
**Worst part:** Reinforces "Bitcoin = company" misconception
**Verdict:** Avoid unless absolutely desperate

---

So unless you go DIY, the budget to gift Bitcoin + book is going to be more than $25.

